---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="light">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body class="min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-base-100 text-base-content">
		<Header />
		<main class="flex-grow container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
			<div class="hero min-h-[60vh] bg-base-200 rounded-lg">
				<div class="hero-content text-center">
					<div class="max-w-md">
						<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold">üßë‚ÄçüöÄ Hello, Astronaut!</h1>
						<p class="py-6">
							Welcome to the official <a class="link link-primary" href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> blog starter template. This
							template serves as a lightweight, minimally-styled starting point for anyone looking to build
							a personal website, blog, or portfolio with Astro.
						</p>
						<a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">View Blog</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none mt-12">
				<p>
					This template comes with a few integrations already configured in your
					<code class="kbd">astro.config.mjs</code> file. You can customize your setup with
					<a class="link" href="https://astro.build/integrations">Astro Integrations</a> to add tools like Tailwind,
					React, or Vue to your project.
				</p>
				<p>Here are a few ideas on how to get started with the template:</p>
				<ul class="list list-disc pl-5">
					<li>Edit this page in <code class="kbd">src/pages/index.astro</code></li>
					<li>Edit the site header items in <code class="kbd">src/components/Header.astro</code></li>
					<li>Add your name to the footer in <code class="kbd">src/components/Footer.astro</code></li>
					<li>Check out the included blog posts in <code class="kbd">src/content/blog/</code></li>
					<li>Customize the blog post page layout in <code class="kbd">src/layouts/BlogPost.astro</code></li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Have fun! If you get stuck, remember to
					<a class="link" href="https://docs.astro.build/">read the docs</a>
					or <a class="link" href="https://astro.build/chat">join us on Discord</a> to ask questions.
				</p>
				<p>
					Looking for a blog template with a bit more personality? Check out
					<a class="link" href="https://github.com/Charca/astro-blog-template">astro-blog-template</a>
					by <a class="link" href="https://twitter.com/Charca">Maxi Ferreira</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
